Target: OntoBMS is an ontology for Building Management Systems.

Comment: A device that provide a consistent and controlled solution to replacing the air within a space.
Label: Makeup air unit

Comment: A device that condition and distribute air within a building.
Label: Air handling unit

Comment: A device that consists of a fan, a coil, and other components, that are used to cool or heat the air recirculating within a room.
Label: Fan coil unit

Comment: A Variable Air Volume System that vary the airflow at a constant or varying temperature.
Label: VAV system

Comment: A Variable Air Volume System that extracts airflow at a constant or varying temperature.
Label: Exhaust VAV

Comment: A Variable Air Volume System that supplies airflow at a constant or varying temperature.
Label: Supply VAV

Comment: A Constant Air Volume System that supply a constant airflow at a variable temperature.
Label: CAV system

Comment: A separate space provided for air circulation for heating, ventilation, and air-conditioning.
Label: Plenum

Comment: A device that uses venting and air flow to protect users from hazardous substances such as vapors, gases, and particulates.
Label: Fume hood

Comment: A device designed to vent non-toxic vapors like steam, heat and odors.
Label: Canopy hood

Comment: A larger fume hood designed to be able to house large laboratory instruments and equipment.
Label: Walk-in fume hood

Comment: A coil that uses water as a heat transfer medium.
Label: Water coil

Comment: A coil that uses electricity to generate heat for heat transfer purposes.
Label: Electrical coil

Comment: A duct is a conduit or passage used in heating, ventilation, and air conditioning to deliver and remove air.
Label: Duct

Comment: A pipe is a tubular section or hollow cylinder, usually but not necessarily of circular cross-section, used mainly to convey fluids.
Label: Pipe

Comment: A Tee is a connector between pipes to separate or combine some streams.
Label: Tee

Comment: An exhaust fan pull odors, fumes, and moisture from an area and vent them outdoors for removal.
Label: Exhaust fan

Comment: A type of exhaust fan that dilute and disperse potentially hazardous exhaust or fumes quickly and safely.
Label: High plume fan

Comment: The current state of a damper.
Label: Damper state

Comment: The current state of a device at a low level.
Label: Low level state

Comment: The current state of a device at a medium level.
Label: Medium level state

Comment: The current state of a device at a high level.
Label: High level state

Comment: The amount of heat that needs to be added or removed to create the required change in temperature.
Label: Heat duty

Comment: A signal (pressure based) that that can be used to determine the exact position of a damper.
Label: Damper feedback

Comment: A pressure based measurement used to control the volume of air that flows through your HVAC system by providing measurements to control the damper position.
Label: Damper control

Comment: A signal (frequency based) that that can be used to determine the current state of a VSD device (fan etc).
Label: VSD feedback

Comment: A frequency based measurement used to control an AC motor's speed and torque.
Label: VSD control

Comment: A device that captures welding and soldering fumes, gases, vapours and dusts directly at source and can be connected to a central extraction unit via fans or a pipeline.
Label: Extraction arm

Comment: A relationship that describes a device fulfilling an unit operation (Mixing, Separation etc).
Label: realizes

Comment: A relationship that describes the heat duty involved in a temperature change process.
Label: has heat duty

Comment: A relationship that describes a heat duty being comprised of other heat duties.
Label: is composed of

Comment: A relationship describing a flow moving device (e.g. duct) having a directed connection (e.g. streamline) as an input.
Label: has input

Comment: A relationship describing a flow moving device (e.g. duct) having a directed connection (e.g. streamline) as an output.
Label: has output

Comment: A relationship to describe the sash opening of a fumehood as a percentage.
Label: has sash open percentage

Comment: A relationship that describes the flow rate of a substance being conveyed or processed by a HVAC or Flow Moving Device (Duct etc) or it can be used to describe the volumetric flow rate of a convective transport rate.
Label: has flow rate

Comment: A relationship that describes the flow rate of air being conveyed or processed by a HVAC or Flow Moving Device (Duct etc) or it can be used to describe the volumetric air flow rate of a convective transport rate.
Label: has air flow rate

Comment: A relationship that describes the flow rate of water being conveyed or processed by a HVAC or Flow Moving Device (Pipe etc) or it can be used to describe the volumetric water flow rate of a convective transport rate.
Label: has water flow rate

Comment: A relationship that describes the sustance being conveyed by a flow moving device (e.g. duct).
Label: conveys

Comment: A relationship that describes a low level state of a multi-level state.
Label: has low level state

Comment: A relationship that describes a medium level state of a multi-level state.
Label: has medium level state

Comment: A relationship that describes a high level state of a multi-level state.
Label: has high level state

Comment: A relationship that describes a HVAC device supplying air to a flow moving device.
Label: supplies air to

Comment: A relationship that describes a HVAC device removing air from a flow moving device or a flow treatment device.
Label: extracts air from

Comment: A relationship that describes the opening of an extraction arm in percentage.
Label: has opening

Comment: A relationship that describes the Bacnet Device ID assigned to an entity.
Label: has bacnet device ID

Comment: A relationship that describes the Bacnet Object ID assigned to an entity.
Label: has bacnet object ID
